Use Subject to and Conditions








      The AARP Automobile & Homeowners Insurance Program from The Hartford is underwritten by Hartford Fire Insurance Company and its affiliates, One Hartford Plaza, Hartford CT 06155.  In California, the Auto Program is unwritten by Hartford Casualty Insurance Company, and the Home Program is underwritten by Trumbull Insurance Company.  In Washington, the Auto program is underwritten by Trumbull Insurance Company, and the Home Program is underwritten by Hartford Underwriters Insurance Company.  In Minnesota, the Auto Program is underwritten by Trumbull Insurance Company, and the Home Program is underwritten by Twin City Fire Insurance Company.  In Pennsylvania, the Auto Program is underwritten by Hartford Underwriters Insurance Company, and the Home Program is underwritten by Hartford Insurance Company of Illinois.  Auto program not available in Massachusetts.  Homeowners product is not available in all areas, including the state of Florida.  AARP does not employ or endorse agents or brokers.  AARP and its affiliates are not insurers.  Paid endorsement.  The Hartford pays royalty fees to AARP for the use of its intellectual property.  These fees are used for the general purposes of AARP.  AARP membership is required for Program eligibility in most states.  Applicants are individually underwritten and some may not qualify.  Specific features, credits, and discounts may vary and may not be available in all states in accordance with state filings and applicable law.  You have the option of purchasing a policy directly from The Hartford.  Your price, however, could vary, and you will not have the advice, counsel or services of your independent agent. 
    

1In Texas, the auto program is underwritten by Southern County Mutual Insurance Company through Hartford of Texas General Agency, Inc.  Hartford Fire Insurance Company and its affiliates are not financially responsible for insurance products underwritten and issued by Southern County Mutual Insurance Company. In Texas, the home program is underwritten by Twin City Fire Insurance Company.
    

† If you are age 50 or older, once you’re insured through this Program for at least 60 days, you cannot be refused renewal as long as applicable premiums are paid when due.  Also, you and other customary drivers of your vehicles must retain valid licenses, remain physically and mentally capable of operating an automobile, have no convictions for driving while intoxicated and must not have obtained your policy through material misrepresentation.  Benefit currently not available in HI, MI, NH and NC.
    

§§ Limitations apply
    

* Savings amounts are averages based on information from The Hartford’s AARP Auto Insurance Program customers who became new auto insurance policyholders between1/1/15 and 12/30/15 and provided data regarding their savings [and prior carrier].  This data is also used to determine the number/percentage of individuals who saved money when they switched.  Your savings may vary.
    

‡ Some benefits, such as the Contents Replacement Coverage, are only available with the optional Home  Advantage Plus package. A policy without these added benefits is also available.
    

** When you choose this optional coverage and insure your home for 100% of its replacement cost, if you have a total loss on your home, The Hartford will pay the full cost to rebuild it, even if it costs up to 150% of your home insurance policy’s Coverage A amount.  (This coverage may not be available in all states.  In some states The Hartford will pay up to 125% your coverage limits.).
    
















